enable smooth font rendering in arch-linux
when installing gnome the .Xresources file may be overwritten and antialiasing disabled
thus add (or edit) following in .Xresources

Xft.lcdfilter: lcddefault
Xft.antialias: true
Xft.autohint: 0
Xft.hinting: true
Xft.hintstyle: hintslight
Xft.rgba: rgb
Xft.dpi: 96

the run: xrdb -merge ~/.Xresources
or add that line to startup script of WM
